      • getForeignKeyFieldsInCache

        protected MetafieldIdList getForeignKeyFieldsInCache()
        Returns a list of foreign key metafields which are to be cached as part of the cached entity. These are qualified fields with navigation path starting from the cached entity. For example, if as part of cached entity "UnitYardVisit", field equipment type id of the UYV is required, then the field to be added to list of fields to be fetched will be "uyvUfv.ufvUnit.unitPrimaryUe.ueEquipment.eqEqtype.eqtypeId" But the actual foreign key field in this case is "uyvUfv.ufvUnit.unitPrimaryUe.ueEquipment.eqEqtype", as this is the field in the "Equipment" entity which holds the reference to "EquipType" entity. So for all the related("compound") fields which are to be cached, the foreign key fields also need to be defined
        Returns:
        a list of foreign key metafields which are to be cached as part of the cached entity. These are qualified fields with navigation path starting from the cached entity.

      • getRelatedEntityNameKeyFieldMap

        protected java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.List<MetafieldId>> getRelatedEntityNameKeyFieldMap()
        Returns a map of related(foreign key) entity name and the metafield(s) where it's value is stored in current entity. Usually there is only one but there can be multiple foreign keys for same entity like a WorkInstruction has multiple fields for Che entity (WI_ITV, WI_CHE, WI_NOMINATED_CHE and so on)
        Returns:
        a map of related(foreign key) entity name and the metafield(s) where it's value is stored in current entity

      • updateFieldsOfComponent

        protected void updateFieldsOfComponent(@NotNull

      • getQualifiedMetafieldIds

        @NotNull
protected java.util.List<MetafieldId> getQualifiedMetafieldIds(MetafieldId inUpdatedMetafieldId,
                                                                         java.lang.String inCachedEntityName,
                                                                         java.lang.String inUpdatedEntityName)
        Returns a qualified metafield id with navigation path from cached entity name to the updated entity name For example, field "eqtypeId" of updated entity "EquipType", given cached entity as "UnitYardVisit" should yield "uyvUfv.ufvUnit.unitPrimaryUe.ueEquipment.eqEqtype.eqtypeId"
        Parameters:
        inUpdatedMetafieldId - field which was updated
        inCachedEntityName - name of the cached entity
        inUpdatedEntityName - entity to which the updated field belongs
        Returns:
        list of qualified metafield id with navigation path from cached entity name to the updated entity name. In most cases a single metafield will be returned. A list is only returned if one entity has multiple foreign key fields pointing to same entity, for example, WorkInstruction entity has multiple fields which hold reference to Che entity (WI_ITV, WI_CHE and so on) A field will only be added to the returned list if it is one of the desired fields.

      • getEstimateObjectSize

        public long getEstimateObjectSize()
        Get estimated size of each object in the cache. Usually it's based on the number of normalized fields of the object value holder Subclasses need to implement this method to give a meaningful size The value is taken from a memory snapshot from yourkit. Each implementation can have different number of fields. Therefore, it's an "estimate" value.
        Returns:
        size in bytes
